[283.49906, "o", "l"]
[283.612752, "o", "\r\n"]
[284.271027, "o", "  {\r\n      \"total_contributions\": 10,\r\n      \"eval_count\": 4,\r\n      \"attack_map_count\": 3,\r\n      \"ioc_bundle_count\": 3,\r\n      \"unique_vendors\": 3,\r\n      \"unique_techniques\": 5,\r\n      \"merkle_root\": \"75c7a98a9fe341fa71d82552f36a62f8e50d108fdf3c103fb3cae23264ef080d\",\r\n      \"pending_categories\": 0,\r\n      \"revealed_categories\": 0\r\n  }\r\n"]
[287.279639, "o", "\r\n  Every contribution is committed to a Merkle tree.\r\n"]
[289.288567, "o", "\r\n  The Merkle root is a fingerprint of ALL contributions.\r\n"]
[291.299029, "o", "\r\n  Change one value and the root changes — tamper-evident.\r\n"]
[297.318307, "o", "\r\n  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\n"]
[300.3247, "o", "\r\n  Verify the CrowdStrike aggregate is real:\r\n"]
[302.32898, "o", "\r\n  $ curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8799/verify/aggregate/CrowdStrike\r\n"]
[302.458513, "o", "  Contributors: 2\r\n  Merkle root:  75c7a98a9fe341fa71d82552f36a62f8e50d108f...\r\n  Valid:         True\r\n    commitment_count_matches: PASS\r\n    merkle_root_present: PASS\r\n    signature_present: PASS\r\n"]
[302.461349, "o", "\r\n  Three checks, all PASS. The aggregate is mathematically\r\n"]
[304.466192, "o", "\r\n  proven to be computed from real committed contributions.\r\n"]
[306.483164, "o", "\r\n  The server can't inflate the count, alter scores, or\r\n"]
[308.505303, "o", "\r\n  exclude contributions. Math, not promises.\r\n"]
[318.543359, "o", "\r\n  ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\r\n  ║  Plot twist: a new threat actor emerges\r\n"]
[318.543429, "o", "  ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\r\n\r\n"]
[322.55301, "o", "\r\n  Three hospitals independently encounter a new ransomware\r\n"]
[324.564158, "o", "\r\n  group called 'DarkAngel' — but it's not in any public\r\n"]
[326.575722, "o", "\r\n  database yet. How do they surface it collectively without\r\n"]
[328.583534, "o", "\r\n  any of them revealing they were attacked?\r\n"]
[330.592859, "o", "\r\n\r\n  Blind category discovery.\r\n"]
[335.854408, "o", "\r\n  Each hospital hashes the name locally:\r\n"]
[337.85815, "o", "    H = SHA-256(\"DarkAngel\":salt) = 5b67724cd0f0a103ae7129beed5019e2...\r\n"]
[339.369328, "o", "    The server will see this hash. Never the name.\r\n"]
[343.889445, "o", "\r\n"]
[343.889563, "o", "  $ curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8799/category/propose ... (hospital-a)\r\n"]
[344.004436, "o", "  hospital-a: pending (1/3)\r\n"]
[345.011235, "o", "  $ curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8799/category/propose ... (hospital-b)\r\n"]
[345.116648, "o", "  hospital-b: pending (2/3)\r\n"]
[346.127014, "o", "  $ curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8799/category/propose ... (hospital-c)\r\n"]
[346.270356, "o", "  hospital-c: threshold_met (3/3)\r\n"]
[347.277824, "o", "\r\n  Three hospitals submitted the same hash independently.\r\n"]
[349.291682, "o", "\r\n  Threshold met. Now they vote to reveal the name:\r\n"]
[354.315306, "o", "\r\n"]
[354.432463, "o", "  hospital-a: vote_recorded \r\n"]
[355.559565, "o", "  hospital-b: revealed darkangel\r\n"]
[356.571356, "o", "\r\n  'DarkAngel' is now a public category. The collective\r\n"]
[358.582285, "o", "\r\n  can aggregate data about it. The server learned the name\r\n"]
[360.591122, "o", "\r\n  only because 3 hospitals independently confirmed it —\r\n"]
[362.602605, "o", "\r\n  and 2 voted to make it public.\r\n"]
[372.630955, "o", "\r\n  ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\r\n  ║  What each side knows\r\n  ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\r\n\r\n"]
[376.641428, "o", "  THE SERVER HAS:                THE SERVER CANNOT SEE:\r\n  ─────────────────              ──────────────────────\r\n"]
[376.641486, "o", "  Commitment hashes (SHA-256)    Individual scores\r\n  Running sums per vendor        Which hospital submitted what\r\n  Technique frequency counters   Free-text notes or sigma rules\r\n  Merkle tree                    Raw IOC values (IPs, domains)\r\n  Blind category hashes          Who proposed which category\r\n\r\n"]
[380.65134, "o", "\r\n"]
[380.651402, "o", "  Without nur: each hospital fights alone, misses the\r\n"]
[382.666182, "o", "\r\n  campaign connection, buys tools based on vendor marketing.\r\n"]
[384.6871, "o", "\r\n\r\n  With nur: collaborative defense with mathematical\r\n"]
[386.695136, "o", "\r\n  privacy guarantees. 575 tests. Zero individual values.\r\n"]
[388.705565, "o", "\r\n"]
[394.715162, "o", "  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\r\n  │                                                             │\r\n  │   Attackers share everything.                               │\r\n  │   Defenders share nothing.                                  │\r\n"]
[394.715212, "o", "  │   nur fixes that.                                           │\r\n  │                                                             │\r\n  │   nur.saramena.us · github.com/manizzle/nur                │\r\n  │                                                             │\r\n  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\r\n\r\n"]
